Contains small MATE-SOCS models.

What is MATE-SOCS (System-On-Chip Solver)?

The objective of MATE-SOCS is to provide an solver for electric converter and motor drives that:
1- Enable the simulation on FPGA of arbitrary circuit topologies on FPGA
2- with a unique FPGA bitstream
3- During simulation, parameters can be changed.
4- Between simulations, topology can be changed.

I use HDL Coder in my workflow. This product is really wonderful in my opinion.

The objective is to give more useful time to HIL test engineers like you and me and stop building new bitstream each time there is a change in the model.

Start with myFirstCircuit: it's a buck converter  and passes all HDL Coder verification.
4th : buck converter with transformer
5th circuit: boost converter and PMSM motor with vector drive. 
Would need a nice simulator with CPUs for controllers and mechanical and
FPGA for the motor drive and boost converter.
The 5th model uses 2 SOCS units.

/designs contains HDL Coder results
